Install react

step 1: npm create vite@latest folder-name -- --template react    
step 2: cd folder-name
step 3: install tailwind css or npm install


Install tailwind css

step 1: npm install -D tailwindcss postcss autoprefixer
step 2: npx tailwindcss init -p
step 3: in tailwind.config.js file's upade the content part. ->   content: [ "./index.html", "./src/**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx}", ],
step 4: delete all css code in index.css file and add bellow css code " @tailwind base; @tailwind components; @tailwind utilities; "
COPMLETE Tailwind css add in react. Tailwind link: https://tailwindcss.com/docs/guides/vite



Install daisyUI

step 1: npm i -D daisyui@latest
step 2: in tailwind.config.js file's plugins part update.  ->   plugins: [require("daisyui")],
step 3: in .eslintrc.cjs file's env part update. -> node:true,
COMPLETE DaisyUi add in react. DaisyUI link: https://daisyui.com/docs/install/


Install react-icon

step 1: npm install react-icons
step 2: import selected icon copmonent.
step 3: use the icon component.
COMPLETE React icon add. React icon link: https://react-icons-v2.vercel.app/


Install Recharts
step 1: npm install recharts
step 2: copy the code and use.
COMPLETE rechart add. Rechart link: https://recharts.org/en-US/guide/installation


Insatall Axios
step 1: npm install axios
COMPLETE Axios add. Axios link: https://axios-http.com/docs/intro
Note : use of axios see the Axios.jsx file in this project.


Install awesome-react-components
Setp 1: go this link : https://github.com/brillout/awesome-react-components and find what you want and follow the ruls and use this part


Some command for react project:
npm run dev -> for run this project.
npm run build -> for making dist file. when we host react project in 3rd party service (linke netlyfly) this time we upload thie dist file only.
surge dist -> for hote the surge site.







 